# Custom Theme System — Implementation Plan

## Context

T3 Code currently has a minimal light/dark/system theme toggle (`apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`) that only switches the `.dark` CSS class on `<html>`. The task is to replace this with a richer named-theme system: three built-in palettes ("t3-dark", "t3-light", "t3-midnight") with per-component color tokens (sidebar, editor, terminal, status bar), a React Context provider, a `useTheme` hook, and a visual theme selector with preview swatches.

Constraints: no new dependencies, no build config changes.

---

## Architecture Overview

```
packages/shared/src/theme.ts          ← ThemeId type, ThemeDefinition interface,
                                         THEMES map, THEME_IDS, DEFAULT_THEME_ID
packages/shared/package.json          ← add "./theme" subpath export

apps/web/src/contexts/ThemeContext.tsx ← ThemeContext, ThemeProvider (React Context)
apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts        ← rewritten: thin wrapper over ThemeContext
apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx ← swatch selector UI
apps/web/src/index.css                ← [data-theme="..."] CSS variable blocks
apps/web/src/router.ts                ← add ThemeProvider to Wrap
apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx ← replace radio group with <ThemeSelector />
```

---

## Step-by-Step Plan

### Step 1 — `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` (new file)

Define all shared theme types and constants. Use plain TypeScript (no Effect Schema — schemas belong in `contracts`; this is a utility module like the others in `shared`).

```ts
export type ThemeId = "t3-dark" | "t3-light" | "t3-midnight";

export interface ThemeColors {
  background: string;   // hex/oklch — used for preview swatches
  foreground: string;
  accent: string;
  sidebar: string;
  editor: string;
  terminal: string;
  statusBar: string;
}

export interface ThemeDefinition {
  id: ThemeId;
  label: string;
  description: string;
  isDark: boolean;      // governs .dark class for Tailwind dark: utilities
  colors: ThemeColors;  // representative values for swatch preview
}

export const THEMES: Readonly<Record<ThemeId, ThemeDefinition>> = {
  "t3-light": { id: "t3-light", label: "T3 Light", description: "Clean light palette.",
    isDark: false, colors: {
      background: "#ffffff", foreground: "#262626", accent: "#3b5bdb",
      sidebar: "#f5f5f5", editor: "#ffffff", terminal: "#1c1c1c", statusBar: "#3b5bdb",
  }},
  "t3-dark": { id: "t3-dark", label: "T3 Dark", description: "Dark theme with a blue accent.",
    isDark: true, colors: {
      background: "#0c0c0c", foreground: "#f5f5f5", accent: "#6b8df7",
      sidebar: "#0f0f0f", editor: "#0c0c0c", terminal: "#000000", statusBar: "#1e3a8a",
  }},
  "t3-midnight": { id: "t3-midnight", label: "T3 Midnight", description: "Deep high-contrast purple-tinted dark.",
    isDark: true, colors: {
      background: "#000005", foreground: "#ffffff", accent: "#a78bfa",
      sidebar: "#07070f", editor: "#000005", terminal: "#000000", statusBar: "#1e1b4b",
  }},
} as const;

export const THEME_IDS = ["t3-light", "t3-dark", "t3-midnight"] as const satisfies readonly ThemeId[];
export const DEFAULT_THEME_ID: ThemeId = "t3-dark";
```

### Step 2 — `packages/shared/package.json`

Add the `./theme` subpath export (same pattern as existing exports):

```json
"./theme": {
  "types": "./src/theme.ts",
  "import": "./src/theme.ts"
}
```

### Step 3 — `apps/web/src/index.css`

#### 3a — Add new CSS custom property defaults to `:root`

Inside `:root { ... }`, add defaults for the five new component-specific tokens (sidebar, editor, terminal, status-bar) so any code path without a `data-theme` attribute still has sane values:

```css
:root {
  /* …existing vars… */
  --sidebar:            var(--background);
  --sidebar-foreground: var(--foreground);
  --editor:             var(--background);
  --editor-foreground:  var(--foreground);
  --terminal:           #1c1c1c;
  --terminal-foreground: #f5f5f5;
  --status-bar:         var(--primary);
  --status-bar-foreground: var(--primary-foreground);

  @variant dark {
    /* …existing dark overrides… */
    --terminal:           #000000;
    --status-bar:         oklch(0.35 0.15 264);
  }
}
```

#### 3b — Add `[data-theme="t3-light"]` block

Overrides all semantic tokens + new tokens for the light theme:

```css
[data-theme="t3-light"] {
  color-scheme: light;
  --background:          var(--color-white);
  --foreground:          var(--color-neutral-800);
  --card:                var(--color-white);
  --card-foreground:     var(--color-neutral-800);
  --popover:             var(--color-white);
  --popover-foreground:  var(--color-neutral-800);
  --primary:             oklch(0.488 0.217 264);
  --primary-foreground:  var(--color-white);
  --secondary:           --alpha(var(--color-black) / 4%);
  --secondary-foreground: var(--color-neutral-800);
  --muted:               --alpha(var(--color-black) / 4%);
  --muted-foreground:    color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-500) 90%, var(--color-black));
  --accent:              --alpha(var(--color-black) / 4%);
  --accent-foreground:   var(--color-neutral-800);
  --destructive:         var(--color-red-500);
  --destructive-foreground: var(--color-red-700);
  --border:              --alpha(var(--color-black) / 8%);
  --input:               --alpha(var(--color-black) / 10%);
  --ring:                oklch(0.488 0.217 264);
  --info:                var(--color-blue-500);
  --info-foreground:     var(--color-blue-700);
  --success:             var(--color-emerald-500);
  --success-foreground:  var(--color-emerald-700);
  --warning:             var(--color-amber-500);
  --warning-foreground:  var(--color-amber-700);
  /* Component-specific */
  --sidebar:             #f5f5f5;
  --sidebar-foreground:  var(--color-neutral-700);
  --editor:              var(--color-white);
  --editor-foreground:   var(--color-neutral-800);
  --terminal:            #1c1c1c;
  --terminal-foreground: #f5f5f5;
  --status-bar:          oklch(0.488 0.217 264);
  --status-bar-foreground: var(--color-white);
}
```

#### 3c — Add `[data-theme="t3-dark"]` block

Mirrors the existing `@variant dark` overrides plus new tokens:

```css
[data-theme="t3-dark"] {
  color-scheme: dark;
  --background:          color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 95%, var(--color-white));
  /* …full dark palette matching existing @variant dark values… */
  --sidebar:             color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 98%, var(--color-white));
  --sidebar-foreground:  var(--color-neutral-100);
  --editor:              color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 95%, var(--color-white));
  --editor-foreground:   var(--color-neutral-100);
  --terminal:            #000000;
  --terminal-foreground: #f5f5f5;
  --status-bar:          oklch(0.35 0.15 264);
  --status-bar-foreground: var(--color-white);
}
```

#### 3d — Add `[data-theme="t3-midnight"]` block

Distinct purple-tinted ultra-dark palette:

```css
[data-theme="t3-midnight"] {
  color-scheme: dark;
  --background:          #000005;
  --foreground:          #ffffff;
  --card:                #07070f;
  --popover:             #07070f;
  /* …all semantic tokens with purple-tinted midnight values… */
  --primary:             oklch(0.68 0.22 280);   /* purple-blue */
  --ring:                oklch(0.68 0.22 280);
  --sidebar:             #07070f;
  --sidebar-foreground:  #e0e0ff;
  --editor:              #000005;
  --editor-foreground:   #ffffff;
  --terminal:            #000000;
  --terminal-foreground: #e0e0ff;
  --status-bar:          #1e1b4b;   /* indigo-950 */
  --status-bar-foreground: #c4b5fd;
}
```

### Step 4 — `apps/web/src/contexts/ThemeContext.tsx` (new file)

React Context provider. Applies `data-theme` attribute + syncs `.dark` class. Prevents flash by calling `applyTheme(getStoredThemeId())` at module-load time (same pattern as existing `useTheme.ts`).

```ts
import { createContext, useCallback, useEffect, useState } from "react";
import {
  DEFAULT_THEME_ID, THEME_IDS, THEMES,
  type ThemeDefinition, type ThemeId
} from "@t3tools/shared/theme";

const STORAGE_KEY = "t3code:color-theme";

function getStoredThemeId(): ThemeId {
  try {
    const raw = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);
    if (raw && (THEME_IDS as readonly string[]).includes(raw)) return raw as ThemeId;
  } catch { /* quota / SSR */ }
  return DEFAULT_THEME_ID;
}

function applyTheme(id: ThemeId, suppressTransitions = false): void {
  if (suppressTransitions) document.documentElement.classList.add("no-transitions");
  document.documentElement.setAttribute("data-theme", id);
  document.documentElement.classList.toggle("dark", THEMES[id].isDark);
  if (suppressTransitions) {
    // oxlint-disable-next-line no-unused-expressions
    document.documentElement.offsetHeight; // force reflow
    requestAnimationFrame(() => document.documentElement.classList.remove("no-transitions"));
  }
}

// Prevent flash on page load — runs before React renders
applyTheme(getStoredThemeId());

export interface ThemeContextValue {
  themeId: ThemeId;
  theme: ThemeDefinition;
  setTheme: (id: ThemeId) => void;
}

export const ThemeContext = createContext<ThemeContextValue | null>(null);

export function ThemeProvider({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const [themeId, setThemeIdState] = useState<ThemeId>(getStoredThemeId);

  const setTheme = useCallback((id: ThemeId) => {
    try { localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, id); } catch { /* ignore */ }
    applyTheme(id, true);
    setThemeIdState(id);
  }, []);

  // Cross-tab sync
  useEffect(() => {
    const handler = (e: StorageEvent) => {
      if (e.key !== STORAGE_KEY) return;
      const id = getStoredThemeId();
      applyTheme(id, true);
      setThemeIdState(id);
    };
    window.addEventListener("storage", handler);
    return () => window.removeEventListener("storage", handler);
  }, []);

  // Keep DOM in sync on mount/change
  useEffect(() => { applyTheme(themeId); }, [themeId]);

  return (
    <ThemeContext.Provider value={{ themeId, theme: THEMES[themeId], setTheme }}>
      {children}
    </ThemeContext.Provider>
  );
}
```

### Step 5 — `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` (rewrite)

Replace the existing module-level-state implementation with a thin context consumer. Export the same `setTheme` name to minimize callsite churn; add `themeId` and `theme` to the return value.

```ts
import { useContext } from "react";
import { ThemeContext } from "../contexts/ThemeContext";

export function useTheme() {
  const ctx = useContext(ThemeContext);
  if (!ctx) throw new Error("useTheme must be used within <ThemeProvider>");
  return ctx;  // { themeId, theme, setTheme }
}
```

### Step 6 — `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` (new file)

Swatch grid. Each card shows a mini layout preview (sidebar strip, editor area, terminal strip, status bar strip, accent dot). Uses only Tailwind classes + inline `style` for the swatch colors (no new dependencies).

```tsx
import { THEME_IDS, THEMES } from "@t3tools/shared/theme";
import { useTheme } from "../hooks/useTheme";

export function ThemeSelector() {
  const { themeId, setTheme } = useTheme();

  return (
    <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Color theme">
      {THEME_IDS.map((id) => {
        const def = THEMES[id];
        const selected = themeId === id;
        return (
          <button
            key={id}
            type="button"
            role="radio"
            aria-checked={selected}
            onClick={() => setTheme(id)}
            className={`flex flex-col gap-2 rounded-xl border p-3 text-left transition-colors
              ${selected
                ? "border-primary/60 bg-primary/8 ring-1 ring-primary/20"
                : "border-border bg-background hover:bg-accent"}`}
          >
            {/* ── Preview swatch ── */}
            <div
              className="relative h-14 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-black/10"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              {/* Editor / main area */}
              <div
                className="absolute inset-0"
                style={{ background: def.colors.editor }}
              />
              {/* Sidebar strip (left 22%) */}
              <div
                className="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 w-[22%]"
                style={{ background: def.colors.sidebar }}
              />
              {/* Status bar (bottom 14%) */}
              <div
                className="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-[14%]"
